Honored to be a part of this incredible wedding featured in @vogueindia :) 

I want to take a second to acknowledge the importance of fusion weddings, blending our cultures, and showing the world two sides can co-exist regardless of cultural & ethnic differences. 

My core journey as an artist started by combining western sounds with our traditional Indian elements, showcasing a landscape of music to be enjoyed by the ears of many. 

Multicultural weddings will always have a special place in my heart ❤️
Thank you to this beautiful couple for putting your musical trust in my hands and to everyone involved 🙏🏽

It’s not often I get the opportunity to play classical. I haven’t opened up much about my background, but I grew up teaching myself how to play, never having a teacher or an Ustaad, hence creating my own unique style of playing. I’ve explored with many genres of music, but when I get the chance to play classically, I particularly love it because of how much it feeds the soul 🤍
